author: dlr
msg: A follow-up to r18972, adding some commentary from that commit's
change log message as a source-level comment.
* subversion/libsvn_repos/hooks.c
(check_hook_cmd): Add comment indicating that the presence of ".wsf"
files in the "check_extns" list obviates the need for ".js" and
".vbs" files.
Suggested by: philip

author: kfogel
msg: Make vc-svn parse the output of svn status -v correctly when a file has been
merged but not yet committed.  It then has a valid last-committed
revision but not a working-copy revision; treat it as newly added file.
Patch by: "Mattias Engdegård" <mattias@virtutech.se>
* contrib/client-side/vc-svn.el
(vc-svn-parse-status): Make regexp more tolerant of last-committed revision.
